        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "1. Given a weight function $\\rho ( x ) > 0$ , let the inner-product corresponding to $\\rho ( x )$ be defined as follows: ",
        "bbox": [
            191,
            323,
            803,
            357
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\n(f, g) := \\int_ {a} ^ {b} \\rho (x) f (x) g (x) \\mathrm {d} x,\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            371,
            363,
            626,
            401
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "and let $\\| f \\| : = ( f , f )$ . ",
        "bbox": [
            193,
            407,
            383,
            426
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "(1) Define a sequence of polynomials as follows: ",
        "bbox": [
            223,
            429,
            640,
            447
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\n\\begin{array}{l} p _ {0} (x) = 1, \\quad p _ {1} (x) = x - a _ {1}, \\\\ p _ {n} (x) = \\left(x - a _ {n}\\right) p _ {n - 1} (x) - b _ {n} p _ {n - 2} (x), \\quad n = 2, 3, \\dots \\\\ \\end{array}\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            265,
            456,
            729,
            492
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "where ",
        "bbox": [
            257,
            501,
            314,
            514
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\na _ {n} = \\frac {\\left(x p _ {n - 1} , p _ {n - 1}\\right)}{\\left(p _ {n - 1} , p _ {n - 1}\\right)}, \\quad n = 1, 2, \\dots\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            336,
            521,
            648,
            557
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\nb _ {n} = \\frac {\\left(x p _ {n - 1} , p _ {n - 2}\\right)}{\\left(p _ {n - 2} , p _ {n - 2}\\right)}, \\quad n = 2, 3, \\dots .\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            337,
            561,
            658,
            596
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Show that $\\{ p _ { n } ( x ) \\}$ is an orthogonal sequence of monic polynomials. ",
        "bbox": [
            255,
            602,
            801,
            634
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "(2) Let $\\{ q _ { n } ( x ) \\}$ be an orthogonal sequence of monic polynomials corresponding to the $\\rho$ inner product. (A polynomial is called monic if its leading coefficient is 1.) Show that $\\{ q _ { n } ( x ) \\}$ is unique and it minimizes $\\| q _ { n } \\|$ amongst all monic polynomials of degree $n$ . ",
            "(3) Hence or otherwise, show that if $\\rho ( x ) = 1 / \\sqrt { 1 - x ^ { 2 } }$ and $[ a , b ] =$ $[ - 1 , 1 ]$ , then the corresponding orthogonal sequence is the Chebyshev polynomials: "
        ],
        "bbox": [
            223,
            636,
            811,
            768
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\nT _ {n} (x) = \\cos (n \\operatorname {a r c c o s} x), \\quad n = 0, 1, 2, \\dots .\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            317,
            777,
            678,
            794
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "and the following recurrent formula holds: ",
        "bbox": [
            255,
            802,
            626,
            818
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\nT _ {n + 1} (x) = 2 x T _ {n} (x) - T _ {n - 1} (x), \\quad n = 1, 2, \\dots .\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            299,
            827,
            695,
            845
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "(4) Find the best quadratic approximation to $f ( x ) = x ^ { 3 }$ on $[ - 1 , 1 ]$ using $\\rho ( x ) = 1 / \\sqrt { 1 - x ^ { 2 } }$ . ",
        "bbox": [
