        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            342,
            158,
            650,
            190
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "and ",
        "bbox": [
            193,
            193,
            231,
            208
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\np (1) = 1, \\qquad q (1) = 2,\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            394,
            209,
            598,
            227
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "find $p ( 0 ) - q ( 0 )$ ",
        "bbox": [
            193,
            229,
            337,
            246
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "3. Lay aside $m$ black balls and $n$ red balls in a jug. Supposes $1 \\leq r \\leq$ $k \\leq n$ . Each time one draws a ball from the jug at random. ",
        "bbox": [
            191,
            252,
            801,
            285
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "1) If each time one draws a ball without return, what is the probability that in the $k$ -th time of drawing one obtains exactly the $r$ -th red ball? ",
            "2) If each time one draws a ball with return, what is the probability that in the first $k$ times of drawings one obtained totally an odd number of red balls? "
        ],
        "bbox": [
            230,
            288,
            801,
            387
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "4. Let $X$ and $Y$ be independent and identically distributed random variables. Show that ",
        "bbox": [
            191,
            394,
            801,
            426
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\nE [ | X + Y | ] \\geq E [ | X | ].\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            403,
            432,
            591,
            451
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Hint: Consider separately two cases: $E [ X ^ { + } ] \\geq E [ X ^ { - } ]$ and $E [ X ^ { + } ] <$ $E [ X ^ { - } ]$ . ",
        "bbox": [
            193,
            454,
            801,
            489
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "5. Suppose that $X _ { 1 } , \\cdots , X _ { n }$ are a random sample from the Bernoulli distribution with probability of success $p _ { 1 }$ and $Y _ { 1 } , \\cdots , Y _ { n }$ be an independent random sample from the Bernoulli distribution with probability of success $p _ { 2 }$ . ",
        "bbox": [
            191,
            495,
            801,
            562
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "(a) Give a minimum sufficient statistic and the UMVU (uniformly minimum variance unbiased) estimator for $\\theta = p _ { 1 } - p _ { 2 }$ . ",
            "(b) Give the Cramer-Rao bound for the variance of the unbiased estimators for $v ( p _ { 1 } ) = p _ { 1 } ( 1 - p _ { 1 } )$ or the UMVU estimator for $v ( p _ { 1 } )$ . ",
            "(c) Compute the asymptotic power of the test with critical region "
        ],
        "bbox": [
            221,
            564,
            801,
            664
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\n| \\sqrt {n} (\\hat {p _ {1}} - \\hat {p _ {2}}) / \\sqrt {2 \\hat {p} \\hat {q}} | \\geq z _ {1 - \\alpha}\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            376,
            669,
            618,
            690
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "when $p _ { 1 } = p$ and $p _ { 2 } = p + n ^ { - 1 / 2 } \\Delta$ , where $\\hat { p } = 0 . 5 \\hat { p } _ { 1 } + 0 . 5 \\hat { p } _ { 2 }$ ",
        "bbox": [
